  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `geth 1.6.5`\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nI have more different platform all node wallet. on Linux, Windows, Mac.\r\nOn one linux, The chaindata folders size is `148G+`;\r\nother Linux, The chaindata folders size is `80G+`, `100G+`, etc... and I set a new server chaindata folder size is `55G+` at 2 days ago.\r\n**bigest**:\r\n```bash\r\n~/.ethereum/geth/chaindata# du -sh\r\n148G    .\r\n~/.ethereum/geth/chaindata# ls | wc -l\r\n75232\r\n```\r\n**smallest**:\r\n```bash\r\n~/.ethereum/geth/chaindata# du -sh\r\n55G     .\r\n~/.ethereum/geth/chaindata# ls | wc -l\r\n30185\r\n```\r\nthe same of start up agrs, all is Ubuntu.\r\n\r\nMy start up args:\r\n```bash\r\nnohup ./geth --rpcaddr 0.0.0.0 --rpc --rpcport 22333 --rpccorsdomain \"http://localhost:3000\" --rpc    api \"eth,net,web3,personal\" &\r\n```\r\n`They are all in good condition`\r\n\r\nThe difference is so great, I don't understand.\r\nthe bigest folder is 148G+ and the smallest is 54G+, Nearly 3 times as much space.\r\nShouldn't the BlockChain data be the same?\r\n\r\nIs there any unnecessary data inside the chain?\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nShouldn't it be all the same of chaindata?\r\n\r\n",
