    "body": "When you start a new geth on a fresh computer it doesn't download the entire blockchain. \r\n\r\nIf you did your sync using --fast it only downloads the receipts. [This thread talked about it a bit more.](https://ethereum.stackexchange.com/questions/1161/what-is-geths-fast-sync-and-why-is-it-faster)\r\n\r\n`Instead of processing the entire block-chain one link at a time, and replay all transactions that ever happened in history, fast syncing downloads the transaction receipts along the blocks, and pulls an entire recent state database.`",
